      "rationale": "The five flow-speed combinations used in validation (1.5–6.0 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) span the CPB clinical operating envelope. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water, viscosity 3.5 mPa·s) replicates physiological viscosity within 5%. Boundary conditions are confirmed to match within ±8% of COU values."
